"title": "7943: ministry, in the church",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7943",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The regular ministry of officially appointed or recognised ministers is a particular instance of the duty and call of all God's people.</p>\n<h2>The responsibilities of those in recognised ministry</h2>\n<h3>As shepherds</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:28\">ACT 20:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:2\">1PE 5:2</a></p>\n<h3>As watchmen</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:17\">HEB 13:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:17\">ROM 16:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:2\">PHP 3:2</a></p>\n<h3>As teachers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:2\">1TI 3:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:2\">2TI 2:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:24\">2TI 2:24</a></p>\n<h3>As examples</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:16\">1TI 4:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:28\">ACT 20:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:3\">1PE 5:3</a></p>\n<h2>What believers owe to those with recognised ministries</h2>\n<h3>Respect</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:12-1Thess5:13\">1TH 5:12–5:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:29\">PHP 2:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:17\">1TI 5:17</a></p>\n<h3>Obedience</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:17\">HEB 13:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor16:15-1Cor16:16\">1CO 16:15–16:16</a></p>\n<h3>Support</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:14\">1CO 9:14</a></strong> <em>Despite Jesus Christ's command, Paul did not claim his rights in this matter, but supported himself as a tentmaker.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:7\">LUK 10:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:6\">GAL 6:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:18\">1TI 5:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:4\">DEU 25:4</a></p>\n<h3>Prayer</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:30\">ROM 15:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:19\">EPH 6:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:19\">PHP 1:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:25\">1TH 5:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:18\">HEB 13:18</a></p>\n<h3>Hospitality</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:29-Phil2:30\">PHP 2:29–2:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:14\">GAL 4:14</a></p>\n<h3>Imitation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:7\">HEB 13:7</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Recognised ministers should encourage the ministries of other believers</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col4:17\">COL 4:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:6-Rom12:8\">ROM 12:6–12:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:4-1Cor12:11\">1CO 12:4–12:11</a> <em>The Holy Spirit allocates gifts and enables ministries. No individual has all the gifts; ministry is shared and mutual</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:7\">EPH 4:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:11-Eph4:13\">EPH 4:11–4:13</a></p>\n<h2>The motivation of ministry is mutual love</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:13\">GAL 5:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:10\">ROM 12:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:8\">ROM 13:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:12-Col3:14\">COL 3:12–3:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess3:12\">1TH 3:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:1\">HEB 13:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:22\">1PE 1:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:23\">1JN 3:23</a></p>\n<h2>How love is expressed in mutual ministry</h2>\n<h3>In humility</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:2\">EPH 4:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:10\">ROM 12:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:16\">ROM 12:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:26\">GAL 5:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:5\">1PE 5:5</a></p>\n<h3>In patience</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:14\">1TH 5:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:9\">JAS 5:9</a></p>\n<h3>In acceptance and forbearance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:7\">ROM 15:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:13\">COL 3:13</a></p>\n<h3>In kindness, compassion and forgiveness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:32\">EPH 4:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:13\">COL 3:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:15\">1TH 5:15</a></p>\n<h3>In burden-bearing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:2\">GAL 6:2</a></strong></p>\n<h3>In encouragement</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:11\">1TH 5:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:13\">HEB 3:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:24-Heb10:25\">HEB 10:24–10:25</a></p>\n<h3>In teaching and admonition</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:16\">COL 3:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:14\">ROM 15:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:19\">EPH 5:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:14\">1TH 5:14</a></p>\n<h3>In prayer and confession of sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:16\">JAS 5:16</a></strong></p>\n<h3>In hospitality</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:9\">1PE 4:9</a></strong></p>",
